# Certance Token Kit — .copilotignore
#
# ROLE: Layer 2 — version-controlled convention for agent-mode enforcement.
#
# This file is NOT a first-class GitHub Copilot platform feature.
# GitHub Copilot does not read .copilotignore natively for IDE completions,
# Chat, or standard context exclusion. The platform-level mechanism is
# configured in GitHub repository/organisation settings or via the REST API.
# See .github/copilot-content-exclusion.yml for the authoritative pattern list
# and instructions on applying it through GitHub settings or the API.
#
# WHAT THIS FILE DOES:
# - Serves as a version-controlled, code-reviewable record of intended exclusions.
# - Pairs with AGENTS.md (Layer 3) to close the agent-mode gap where GitHub's
#   standard content exclusion does not apply (Agent Mode, Copilot CLI,
#   Cloud Agents).
# - Can be read by custom PreToolUse hooks to enforce exclusions at runtime
#   in agentic workflows if your team implements that layer.
# - Aligns with .gitignore and .vscode/settings.json so the intent is visible
#   across all three developer-facing config surfaces.
#
# ENTERPRISE POSTURE:
# For guaranteed exclusion across all Copilot surfaces, organisations on
# Copilot Business or Enterprise must configure Layer 1 (GitHub settings/API).
# This file alone is not sufficient for compliance or security governance.
#
# References:
#   https://docs.github.com/en/copilot/concepts/context/content-exclusion
#   https://github.com/orgs/community/discussions/10305 (open since 2022, unresolved)
#   https://blog.cloud-eng.nl/2026/03/13/copilot-content-exclusions-four-layers/
#
# Keep this file in sync with .github/copilot-content-exclusion.yml.

